<font color="#FF0000">SOMETHING IN THE SKY</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  1 22:05:21 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was in the Marine Corp stationed in DaNang from March of 67 to August 67. I experienced a life time of living in those months as did most of the men an women station there. I have a question thats been on my mind for thirty years. Every night at about the same time there was something in the night sky that no one could explain. This object at first glance appeared to be a star, but it wasn't, stars don't move across the horizon at fantastic speeds. It wasn't a satellite, because we could see them in their very predictable paths about every ninety minutes. Also to my knowledge satellites don't reverse, stop or change direction like this object did. It was not a plane, chopper or balloon. There was another curious feature about this object, stay with me on this. When moving objects begin to decelerate they slow down and come to a stop. This thing would accelerate at high speed and just stop. There was no slowing down it just stopped. It would also make right angle turns without slowing down. I have met other people since Viet-Nam who have seen this object. A lot of people saw this in the night skies of Viet-Nam in the summer of 1967. Can some one help me solve this mystery?
<p><code>-- Gangof4@Earthlink.Net  (Chuck Williams) </code><p>


